sql:
SELECT activity_type, COUNT(activity_id) AS activity_count
FROM user_activity
GROUP BY activity_type;

external_knowledge:
- "bustling hubs of trade" metaphorically refers to categories with a high number of products; 
- "more than a half-century's worth of commerce" metaphorically represents having over 500 products in a category;
- "sheer diversity of goods they offer" refers to the count of products in each category;
- "ranked from the most prolific to the least" indicates sorting the result by the number of products in descending order.
